          "Performance Metric: Best Model",
          "Comments",
          "Limitations"
        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "",
          "Performance on next exercise",
          "Correct (1) vs Incorrect (0)",
          "29018 ASSISTments2012 learners, 1709 ASSISTmentsChall learners, 78431 EdNet-KT1 learners",
          "ASSISTments, Santa",
          "Exercise and Answer Sequences, LMS logs, Time between exercises",
          "[Learning unit (E-AT-A), interval time, learner embedding]",
          "Most KT approaches achieve good accuracy from sequences of exercises, but pay little attention to effectively monitoring knowledge states → often the knowledge states are not consistent with the learning process → learners can gain knowledge whether they get a question right or wrong → what can change is the pace at which knowledge is gained.\n\nMoreover, most approaches do not account for obvious factors of learning progress such as forgetting. ",
          "The authors propose a framework that continuously monitors how a student progresses.\n\nTo do that, the authors formalize:\n\n- Basic Learning unit as tuple: Exercise-answer time-Answer\n\n- Learning Gains as normalized difference between post and pre test scores → positive effect on learning progress\n\n- Forgetting as a temporal decay - negative progress \n\n- Student progress as the result of both effects.",
          "The model is composed of 3 modules. For any given timestep:\n\nA Learning gain module followed by a Forgetting Module and Finally a prediction module.\n\nEach learner is represented by an embedding vector which encodes the learning progress of the student.\n\nThere is a Q matrix that encodes exercises and knowledge concepts.\n\nLPKT-S additionally adds a set of student-specific features.",
          "DKT, DKT+, DKVMN, SAKT, CKT, AKT, LPKT, LPKT-S",
          "5-Fold Cross-Validation",
          "AST12\n{RMSE: 0.4065 - LPKT-S, R-Squared: 0.2195 - LPKT-S, AUC: 0.7803 - LPKT-S, Accuracy: 0.7584- LPKT-S}\n\nASTChall\n{RMSE:  0.4160 - LPKT-S, R-Squared: 0.2558 - LPKT-S, AUC: 0.7979 - LPKT-S, Accuracy: 0.7420- LPKT-S}\n\nEdNet-KT1\n{RMSE:  0.4261 - LPKT-S, R-Squared: 0.1976 - LPKT-S, AUC:  0.7662 - LPKT-S, Accuracy:  0.7259- LPKT-S}",
          "Author pros«pose a new model that assists in the continuous modelling of student progress by the addition of different modules. \n\nResults on the 3 datasets show that the model beats AKT which was, at the time, the state of the art model.\n\nAuthors also perform ablation studies to check the impact of the presence/absence of the different modules:\n\n- Forgetting has noticeable negative impact in student performace.\n\n- Modelling learning gains achieves better predictive performance than merely modelling outcomes.\n\n- Interval time and answer time are essential information for modelling.\n\nAuthors also perform exercise clustering.",
          "Room for improvement in the representation of Q-matrix.\n\n"
        ]
      ],
      "index": 9
    }
