    {
      "id": "1944750c-f3ba-80ff-bb2b-eb0241bcb590",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "KT is about tracing a student’s knowledge at any given moment with the rationale that knowing what a student knows and where the knowledge is lacking allows for more effective and efficient pedagogical activities. Most methods assess the correctness of the knowledge model by checking how well the model predicts CFA. However, it does not account for whether the students’ learning process maps into the inferred knowledge state.",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "1944750c-f3ba-80ff-bb2b-eb0241bcb590",
        "parent": {
          "type": "page_id",
          "page_id": "18b4750c-f3ba-807b-8f2d-cd625bdc13f1"
        },
